terms.title: Chronos Time
terms.Text: Chronos () is an ancient Greek word meaning chronological or sequential time

terms.title: Kairos Time
terms.Text: Kairos () is an ancient Greek word meaning the right or opportune moment (the "supreme moment").

terms.title: Prime Virtues
terms.Text: Prime virtues need no further justificationthey are their own justification, which is a way of saying they don't have to do anything to be of value. The value of a prime virtue is inherent.

terms.title: The Learning Circle
terms.Text: A diagram created by Mike Breen (3D Movements) that illustrates the process of change we go through after a Kairos moment.
